The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence at Sargent Metal Fabricators in South Carolina. Pence discusses the progress made by the Trump administration in terms of the economy and job creation, highlighting the passage of tax cuts and the growth of the manufacturing sector. He emphasizes the need for Congress to approve the U.S.-Mexico-Canada Agreement (USMCA), which he describes as the largest trade deal in American history. Pence urges the people of South Carolina to support the USMCA and to contact their elected representatives to push for its approval. He also thanks Governor Henry McMaster and members of Congress for their support of the Trump administration's agenda. Pence concludes by expressing his confidence in the future of South Carolina and the United States.